MEMORY ARCHITECTURE
SHORT MEMORY (SESSION)
CT, active agent, immediate context — lives in SESSION.md files. Resets each session. 
LONG MEMORY (ROLLING — THIS FILE)
Patterns, DM, what worked and failed, Never Again rules. Manually pruned. Kept for months. 
REALLY LONG MEMORY (PERMANENT)
Architecture locks, venture DNA, brand positioning, founding principles — lives in docs/ventures/[name]/CONTEXT.md. Never expires unless the venture pivots. 
PERSISTENT STATE (CROSS-SESSION)
Marcus's cross-session awareness — lives in docs/os/MARCUS_STATE.md. Updated at every session end. Read at every SS before SESSION.md. Tracks: LA venture, in-flight work, waiting work, last agent activated per venture. 
VENTURE MEMORY RULE
Separate storage per venture, unified access through Marcus. 
NA Hourbour memory never cross-contaminates agents Marcus holds the master view — no agent reads another venture's context directly Marcus filters and decides what's relevant before routing to any agent Cross-venture insights are tagged [global] and flagged explicitly only when genuinely transferable 
